In our code we build a recommender system from scratch using alternating least squares (ALS) for the MovieLens 32 million dataset. Our system solves (address) sparse matrix completion with 200,948 users, 84,432 movies, and only 0.19% of possible ratings observed. In any system selling products, popular products occupy one end while a long tail of content remains a heavy tail of products users do not know about but that remains monetizable. To capture this value, we build multiple ALS models starting from simple biases to complex uncertainty quantification. Each model addresses different aspects of the recommendation problem. We hope this creates value for both users discovering content and businesses monetizing their entire catalog.

Small Tips on How to Run Our Code¶

  1. Update the data paths to your MovieLens CSV files in the main function () the last one in our file.

To start We organized our code into separate classes to make it clean and easy to work with. Each model gets its own class, which means: which help use us for instance If our BPR model has a bug, we know exactly where to look - in the BPR class. We don't need to lose our mind through thousands of lines of mixed code.

Our Model Classes¶

  • DataLoader: For loading our 32 million ratings and creates the data structures we need to train our models.
  • BiasOnly: Our simplest baseline using just user/item biases (0.8558 RMSE)
  • Latent: Our main ALS model with embeddings for personalization (0.7716 RMSE)
  • Features: Our solution for cold-start movies with genres (0.7708 RMSE)
  • VI: Our model that provides uncertainty estimates (0.8460 RMSE)
  • BPR: Our approach for implicit feedback when users don't rate (0.9953 AUC)

class DataLoader:
    def __init__(self):
        self.M = 0
        self.N = 0
        self.K = 0
        self.mu = 0.0
        
        self.usermap = {}
        self.itemmap = {}
        self.userlist = []
        self.itemlist = []
        self.titles = {}
        self.genres = []
        self.genremap = {}
        self.genrelist = {}
        self.features = []
        
        self.train = []
        self.test = []
        self.trainitem = []
        self.testitem = []
        
        self.userdeg = []
        self.itemdeg = []
        self.counts = None
        
    def load(self, rpath, mpath):
        print("Loading data...")
        ratings = pd.read_csv(rpath)
        movies = pd.read_csv(mpath)
        
        users = sorted(ratings['userId'].unique())
        items = sorted(ratings['movieId'].unique())
        
        self.M = len(users)
        self.N = len(items)
        
        self.usermap = {uid: i for i, uid in enumerate(users)}
        self.itemmap = {mid: i for i, mid in enumerate(items)}
        self.userlist = users
        self.itemlist = items
        self.titles = dict(zip(movies['movieId'], movies['title']))
        
        self.processgenres(movies)
        self.split(ratings)
        
        self.userdeg = [len(self.train[u]) + len(self.test[u]) for u in range(self.M)]
        self.itemdeg = [len(self.trainitem[i]) + len(self.testitem[i]) for i in range(self.N)]
        self.counts = np.array(self.itemdeg)
        
        print(f"Loaded {self.M} users, {self.N} items, {self.K} genres")
        
    def processgenres(self, movies):
        allgenres = set()
        for g in movies['genres'].fillna(''):
            if g and g != '(no genres listed)':
                for genre in g.split('|'):
                    allgenres.add(genre)
        
        self.genres = sorted(list(allgenres)) if allgenres else ['Unknown']
        self.K = len(self.genres)
        self.genremap = {g: i for i, g in enumerate(self.genres)}
        self.genrelist = {i: g for g, i in self.genremap.items()}
        
        self.features = []
        for mid in self.itemlist:
            row = movies[movies['movieId'] == mid]
            if len(row) > 0:
                gstr = str(row.iloc[0]['genres'])
                if gstr != '(no genres listed)' and gstr != 'nan':
                    idxs = [self.genremap[g] for g in gstr.split('|') if g in self.genremap]
                    self.features.append(idxs)
                else:
                    self.features.append([])
            else:
                self.features.append([])
                
    def split(self, ratings):
        self.train = [[] for u in range(self.M)]
        self.test = [[] for u in range(self.M)]
        self.trainitem = [[] for i in range(self.N)]
        self.testitem = [[] for i in range(self.N)]
        
        for idx, row in ratings.iterrows():
            u = self.usermap[row['userId']]
            i = self.itemmap[row['movieId']]
            r = float(row['rating'])
            
            if np.random.rand() < 0.9:
                self.train[u].append((i, r))
                self.trainitem[i].append((u, r))
            else:
                self.test[u].append((i, r))
                self.testitem[i].append((u, r))
        
        trainratings = []
        for u in range(self.M):
            for i, r in self.train[u]:
                trainratings.append(r)
        self.mu = np.mean(trainratings) if trainratings else 3.5
    
    def save(self, filepath):
        with open(filepath, 'wb') as f:
            pickle.dump(self.__dict__, f)
        print(f"Data saved to {filepath}")
    
    def loadprocessed(self, filepath):
        with open(filepath, 'rb') as f:
            saved_data = pickle.load(f)
        self.__dict__.update(saved_data)
        print(f"Data loaded from {filepath}")


def checkconsistency(data):
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("DATA CONSISTENCY CHECK")
    print("="*60)

    if not hasattr(data, 'train'):
        print("Data not loaded yet. Please check file paths.")
        return False

    assert len(data.train) == data.M, "Train user data mismatch"
    assert len(data.test)  == data.M, "Test user data mismatch"
    print(f" Dimensions: {data.M} users, {data.N} items, {data.K} genres")

    traincount = sum(len(data.train[u]) for u in range(data.M))
    testcount = sum(len(data.test[u]) for u in range(data.M))
    total = traincount + testcount
    print(f" Ratings: {total:,} total ({traincount:,} train, {testcount:,} test)")

    denom = data.M * data.N
    sparsity = 100 * (1 - total / denom) if denom > 0 else float('nan')
    print(f"Sparsity: {sparsity:.2f}%")

    emptyusers = sum(1 for u in range(data.M) if len(data.train[u]) == 0)
    item_counts = [0] * data.N
    for u in range(data.M):
        for i, r in data.train[u]:
            if 0 <= i < data.N:
                item_counts[i] = item_counts[i] + 1
    cold_items = sum(1 for c in item_counts if c == 0)
    if emptyusers > 0 or cold_items > 0:
        print(f" Cold start: {emptyusers} users, {cold_items} items")

    if hasattr(data, 'mu'):
        print(f"Global mean μ: {data.mu:.3f}")
    else:
        ratings = [r for u in range(data.M) for (i, r) in data.train[u]]
        if ratings:
            mu = sum(ratings) / len(ratings)
            print(f"Global mean μ (train): {mu:.3f}")

    print("Data loaded successfully!")
    return True

BiasOnly: Here we have our baseline model that learn only user and item biases in our f: $\hat{r}_{ui} = \mu + b_u + b_i$.

class BiasOnly:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.bu = None
        self.bi = None
        self.rmsetrain = []
        self.rmsetest = []
        self.losshistory = []
        
    def computermse(self, dataset):
        errors = []
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i]
                errors.append((r - pred) ** 2)
        return np.sqrt(np.mean(errors)) if errors else 0
    
    def computeloss(self, dataset):
        dataterm = 0
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i]
                dataterm = dataterm + (r - pred) ** 2
        
        regterm = self.gam * (np.sum(self.bu**2) + np.sum(self.bi**2))
        return -0.5 * (self.lam * dataterm + regterm)
        
    def train(self, epochs=10, lam=1.0, gam=0.1):
        self.lam = lam
        self.gam = gam
        
        self.bu = np.zeros(self.data.M)
        self.bi = np.zeros(self.data.N)
        
        self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
        self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
        self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss(self.data.train))
        
        print(f"Initial RMSE: Train={self.rmsetrain[0]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[0]:.4f}")
        
        for ep in range(epochs):
            for u in range(self.data.M):
                items = self.data.train[u]
                if items:
                    residual = sum(r - self.data.mu - self.bi[i] for i, r in items)
                    self.bu[u] = lam * residual / (lam * len(items) + gam)
            
            for i in range(self.data.N):
                users = self.data.trainitem[i]
                if users:
                    residual = sum(r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] for u, r in users)
                    self.bi[i] = lam * residual / (lam * len(users) + gam)
            
            self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
            self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
            self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss(self.data.train))
            
            if (ep + 1) % 5 == 0:
                print(f"Epoch {ep+1}: Train={self.rmsetrain[-1]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[-1]:.4f}")

Here we have our Latent ALS model we extend our baseline ALS to full matrix factorization with our latent factors: $\hat{r}_{ui} = \mu + b_u + b_i + \mathbf{U}_u^T \mathbf{V}_i$.¶

class Latent:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.U = None
        self.V = None
        self.bu = None
        self.bi = None
        self.rmsetrain = []
        self.rmsetest = []
        self.losshistory = []
        
    def computermse(self, dataset):
        errors = []
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                errors.append((r - pred) ** 2)
        return np.sqrt(np.mean(errors)) if errors else 0
    
    def computeloss(self, dataset):
        dataterm = 0
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                dataterm = dataterm + (r - pred) ** 2
        
        regbias = self.gam * (np.sum(self.bu**2) + np.sum(self.bi**2))
        reguv = self.tau * (np.sum(self.U**2) + np.sum(self.V**2))
        return -0.5 * (self.lam * dataterm + regbias + reguv)
        
    def train(self, D=20, epochs=10, lam=0.1, gam=2.5, tau=1.0, verbose=True):
        self.D = D
        self.lam = lam
        self.gam = gam
        self.tau = tau
        
        np.random.seed(42)
        scale = 1.0 / np.sqrt(D)
        self.bu = np.zeros(self.data.M)
        self.bi = np.zeros(self.data.N)
        self.U = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.M, D))
        self.V = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.N, D))
        
        tauI = tau * np.eye(D)
        
        self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
        self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
        self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss(self.data.train))
        
        if verbose:
            print(f"Initial RMSE: Train={self.rmsetrain[0]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[0]:.4f}")
        
        for ep in range(epochs):
            start = time.time()
            
            for u in range(self.data.M):
                items = self.data.train[u]
                if not items:
                    continue
                
                iarr = np.array([i for i, r in items])
                rarr = np.array([r for i, r in items])
                pred = np.dot(self.V[iarr], self.U[u])
                residual = np.sum(rarr - self.data.mu - pred - self.bi[iarr])
                self.bu[u] = lam * residual / (lam * len(items) + gam)
                
                Vbatch = self.V[iarr]
                residuals = rarr - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - self.bi[iarr]
                A = lam * Vbatch.T @ Vbatch + tauI
                b = lam * Vbatch.T @ residuals
                self.U[u] = np.linalg.solve(A, b)
            
            for i in range(self.data.N):
                users = self.data.trainitem[i]
                if not users:
                    continue
                
                uarr = np.array([u for u, r in users])
                rarr = np.array([r for u, r in users])
                pred = np.dot(self.U[uarr], self.V[i])
                residual = np.sum(rarr - self.data.mu - pred - self.bu[uarr])
                self.bi[i] = lam * residual / (lam * len(users) + gam)
                
                Ubatch = self.U[uarr]
                residuals = rarr - self.data.mu - self.bu[uarr] - self.bi[i]
                A = lam * Ubatch.T @ Ubatch + tauI
                b = lam * Ubatch.T @ residuals
                self.V[i] = np.linalg.solve(A, b)
            
            self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
            self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
            self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss(self.data.train))
            
            if verbose and ((ep + 1) % 5 == 0 or ep == 0):
                print(f"Epoch {ep+1}: Time={time.time()-start:.1f}s, "
                      f"Train={self.rmsetrain[-1]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[-1]:.4f}")

class Features:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.U = None
        self.V = None
        self.F = None
        self.bu = None
        self.bi = None
        self.rmsetrain = []
        self.rmsetest = []
        self.losshistory = []
        self.D = None
        
    def getfeaturemean(self, i):
        features = self.data.features[i]
        if not features:
            return np.zeros(self.D)
        return np.sum(self.F[features], axis=0) / np.sqrt(len(features))
        
    def computermse(self, dataset):
        errors = []
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                errors.append((r - pred) ** 2)
        return np.sqrt(np.mean(errors)) if errors else 0
    
    def computeloss(self):
        dataterm = 0
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in self.data.train[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                dataterm = dataterm + (r - pred) ** 2
        
        regbias = self.gam * (np.sum(self.bu**2) + np.sum(self.bi**2))
        regU = self.tau * np.sum(self.U**2)
        
        regV = 0
        for i in range(self.data.N):
            featuremean = self.getfeaturemean(i)
            regV = regV + np.sum((self.V[i] - featuremean)**2)
        regV = regV * self.tau
        
        regF = self.beta * np.sum(self.F**2)
        
        return -0.5 * (self.lam * dataterm + regbias + regU + regV + regF)
        
    def train(self, D=10, epochs=30, lam=0.1, tau=1.0, beta=1.0, gam=2.5):
        self.D = D
        self.lam = lam
        self.tau = tau
        self.beta = beta
        self.gam = gam
        
        np.random.seed(42)
        scale = 1.0 / np.sqrt(D)
        self.bu = np.zeros(self.data.M)
        self.bi = np.zeros(self.data.N)
        self.U = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.M, D))
        self.V = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.N, D))
        self.F = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.K, D))
        
        print(f"\nHierarchical ALS: D={D}, λ={lam}, τ={tau}, β={beta}, γ={gam}")
        print(f"Genre features: {self.data.K} genres")
        
        self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
        self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
        self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss())
        print(f"Initial: Train={self.rmsetrain[0]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[0]:.4f}")
        
        for epoch in range(epochs):
            for u in range(self.data.M):
                items = self.data.train[u]
                if not items:
                    continue
                
                residual = sum(r - self.data.mu - self.bi[i] - np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                             for i, r in items)
                self.bu[u] = lam * residual / (lam * len(items) + gam)
                
                A = tau * np.eye(D)
                b = np.zeros(D)
                for i, r in items:
                    A = A + lam * np.outer(self.V[i], self.V[i])
                    b = b + lam * self.V[i] * (r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - self.bi[i])
                self.U[u] = np.linalg.solve(A, b)
            
            for i in range(self.data.N):
                users = self.data.trainitem[i]
                
                if users:
                    residual = sum(r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - np.dot(self.U[u], self.V[i])
                                 for u, r in users)
                    self.bi[i] = lam * residual / (lam * len(users) + gam)
                
                featuremean = self.getfeaturemean(i)
                A = tau * np.eye(D)
                b = tau * featuremean
                for u, r in users:
                    A = A + lam * np.outer(self.U[u], self.U[u])
                    b = b + lam * self.U[u] * (r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - self.bi[i])
                self.V[i] = np.linalg.solve(A, b)
            
            for k in range(self.data.K):
                movies = [i for i in range(self.data.N) if k in self.data.features[i]]
                if not movies:
                    continue
                
                numer = np.zeros(D)
                denom = beta
                for i in movies:
                    Fi = len(self.data.features[i])
                    if Fi == 0:
                        continue
                    weight = 1.0 / Fi
                    others = [f for f in self.data.features[i] if f != k]
                    residual = self.V[i]
                    if others:
                        residual = residual - np.sum(self.F[others], axis=0) / np.sqrt(Fi)
                    numer = numer + tau * residual / np.sqrt(Fi)
                    denom = denom + tau * weight
                if denom > 0:
                    self.F[k] = numer / denom
            
            self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
            self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
            self.losshistory.append(self.computeloss())
            
            if (epoch + 1) % 10 == 0:
                print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}: Train={self.rmsetrain[-1]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[-1]:.4f}")

VI: Here we have our variational inference model to quantify uncertainty in our predictions, where we maintain distributions over our embeddings rather than point estimates.¶

class VI:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.rmsetrain = []
        self.rmsetest = []
        self.elbohistory = []
        
    def update_user_with_cholesky(self, u):
        items = self.data.train[u]
        if not items:
            return
            
        D = self.D
        
        A = self.tau * np.eye(D)
        b = np.zeros(D)
        
        for i, r in items:
            v_mean = self.mu_V[i]
            v_var = np.diag(self.sigma_V[i])
            
            A = A + self.lam * (np.outer(v_mean, v_mean) + v_var)
            b = b + self.lam * v_mean * (r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - self.bi[i])
        
        try:
            L = scipy.linalg.cholesky(A, lower=True)
            
            y = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, b, lower=True)
            self.mu_U[u] = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y, lower=False)
            
            for d in range(D):
                e_d = np.zeros(D)
                e_d[d] = 1.0
                y_d = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, e_d, lower=True)
                inv_col = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y_d, lower=False)
                self.sigma_U[u, d] = inv_col[d]
                
        except np.linalg.LinAlgError:
            A = A + np.eye(D) 
            L = scipy.linalg.cholesky(A, lower=True)
            y = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, b, lower=True)
            self.mu_U[u] = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y, lower=False)
            self.sigma_U[u] = np.ones(D) / np.diag(A)
    
    def update_item_with_cholesky(self, i):
        users = self.data.trainitem[i]
        if not users:
            return
            
        D = self.D
        
        A = self.tau * np.eye(D)
        b = np.zeros(D)
        
        for u, r in users:
            u_mean = self.mu_U[u]
            u_var = np.diag(self.sigma_U[u])
            
            A = A + self.lam * (np.outer(u_mean, u_mean) + u_var)
            b = b + self.lam * u_mean * (r - self.data.mu - self.bu[u] - self.bi[i])
        
        try:
            L = scipy.linalg.cholesky(A, lower=True)
            
            y = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, b, lower=True)
            self.mu_V[i] = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y, lower=False)
            
            for d in range(D):
                e_d = np.zeros(D)
                e_d[d] = 1.0
                y_d = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, e_d, lower=True)
                inv_col = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y_d, lower=False)
                self.sigma_V[i, d] = inv_col[d]
                
        except np.linalg.LinAlgError:
            A = A + np.eye(D) * 1e-6
            L = scipy.linalg.cholesky(A, lower=True)
            y = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L, b, lower=True)
            self.mu_V[i] = scipy.linalg.solve_triangular(L.T, y, lower=False)
            self.sigma_V[i] = np.ones(D) / np.diag(A)
    
    def computermse(self, dataset):
        errors = []
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in dataset[u]:
                pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.mu_U[u], self.mu_V[i])
                error = r - pred
                errors.append(error * error)
        if errors:
            return np.sqrt(np.mean(errors))
        else:
            return 0
    
    def computeelbo(self):
        dataterm = 0.0
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            for i, r in self.data.train[u]:
                mean_pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.mu_U[u], self.mu_V[i])
                var_pred = np.sum(self.sigma_U[u] * self.mu_V[i] * self.mu_V[i])
                var_pred = var_pred + np.sum(self.mu_U[u] * self.mu_U[u] * self.sigma_V[i])
                var_pred = var_pred + np.sum(self.sigma_U[u] * self.sigma_V[i])
                residual = r - mean_pred
                dataterm = dataterm - 0.5 * self.lam * (residual * residual + var_pred)
        
        kl_u = 0.0
        for u in range(self.data.M):
            kl_u = kl_u + 0.5 * self.tau * np.sum(self.mu_U[u] * self.mu_U[u])
            kl_u = kl_u + 0.5 * self.tau * np.sum(self.sigma_U[u])
            kl_u = kl_u - 0.5 * np.sum(np.log(self.sigma_U[u] + 1e-10))
            kl_u = kl_u - 0.5 * self.D
        
        kl_v = 0.0
        for i in range(self.data.N):
            kl_v = kl_v + 0.5 * self.tau * np.sum(self.mu_V[i] * self.mu_V[i])
            kl_v = kl_v + 0.5 * self.tau * np.sum(self.sigma_V[i])
            kl_v = kl_v - 0.5 * np.sum(np.log(self.sigma_V[i] + 1e-10))
            kl_v = kl_v - 0.5 * self.D
        
        return dataterm - kl_u - kl_v
    
    def train(self, D=20, epochs=50, lam=0.1, tau=1.0, gam=2.5, verbose=True):
        self.D = D
        self.lam = lam
        self.tau = tau
        self.gam = gam
        
        np.random.seed(42)
        scale = 1.0 / np.sqrt(D)
        
        self.mu_U = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.M, D))
        self.mu_V = np.random.normal(0, scale, (self.data.N, D))
        self.sigma_U = np.ones((self.data.M, D)) * scale * scale
        self.sigma_V = np.ones((self.data.N, D)) * scale * scale
        self.bu = np.zeros(self.data.M)
        self.bi = np.zeros(self.data.N)
        
        self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
        self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
        self.elbohistory.append(self.computeelbo())
        
        if verbose:
            print(f"\nVariational Inference with Cholesky")
            print(f"D={D}, λ={lam}, τ={tau}, γ={gam}")
            print(f"Initial RMSE: Train={self.rmsetrain[0]:.4f}, Test={self.rmsetest[0]:.4f}")
        
        for epoch in range(epochs):
            start = time.time()
            
            for u in range(self.data.M):
                items = self.data.train[u]
                if items:
                    residual = 0
                    for i, r in items:
                        pred = self.data.mu + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.mu_U[u], self.mu_V[i])
                        residual = residual + (r - pred)
                    self.bu[u] = lam * residual / (lam * len(items) + gam)
            
            for i in range(self.data.N):
                users = self.data.trainitem[i]
                if users:
                    residual = 0
                    for u, r in users:
                        pred = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + np.dot(self.mu_U[u], self.mu_V[i])
                        residual = residual + (r - pred)
                    self.bi[i] = lam * residual / (lam * len(users) + gam)
            
            for u in range(self.data.M):
                self.update_user_with_cholesky(u)
                
            for i in range(self.data.N):
                self.update_item_with_cholesky(i)
            
            self.rmsetrain.append(self.computermse(self.data.train))
            self.rmsetest.append(self.computermse(self.data.test))
            self.elbohistory.append(self.computeelbo())
            
            if verbose and ((epoch + 1) % 10 == 0 or epoch == 0):
                elbo = self.elbohistory[-1]
                train_rmse = self.rmsetrain[-1]
                test_rmse = self.rmsetest[-1]
                elapsed = time.time() - start
                print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}: Time={elapsed:.1f}s, Train={train_rmse:.4f}, Test={test_rmse:.4f}, ELBO={elbo:.0f}")
    
    def predict_with_uncertainty(self, u, i):
        mean = self.data.mu + self.bu[u] + self.bi[i] + np.dot(self.mu_U[u], self.mu_V[i])
        
        var = np.sum(self.sigma_U[u] * self.mu_V[i] * self.mu_V[i])
        var = var + np.sum(self.mu_U[u] * self.mu_U[u] * self.sigma_V[i])
        var = var + np.sum(self.sigma_U[u] * self.sigma_V[i])
        
        if var > 0:
            std = np.sqrt(var)
        else:
            std = 0.0
        
        return mean, std
    
    def recommend_with_uncertainty(self, user_id, topk=10):
        scores = []
        
        for item_id in range(self.data.N):
            if hasattr(self.data, 'counts'):
                if self.data.counts[item_id] >= 50:
                    mean_score = np.dot(self.mu_U[user_id], self.mu_V[item_id])
                    
                    var_penalty = np.sum(self.sigma_U[user_id] * self.sigma_V[item_id])
                    
                    final_score = mean_score - 0.5 * var_penalty + 0.1 * self.bi[item_id]
                    scores.append((item_id, final_score))
            else:
                mean_score = np.dot(self.mu_U[user_id], self.mu_V[item_id])
                var_penalty = np.sum(self.sigma_U[user_id] * self.sigma_V[item_id])
                final_score = mean_score - 0.5 * var_penalty + 0.1 * self.bi[item_id]
                scores.append((item_id, final_score))
        
        scores.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        
        recommendations = []
        for idx, (item_id, score) in enumerate(scores[:topk]):
            if hasattr(self.data, 'itemlist') and hasattr(self.data, 'titles'):
                movie_id = self.data.itemlist[item_id]
                title = self.data.titles.get(movie_id, "Unknown")
                recommendations.append((movie_id, title, score))
            else:
                recommendations.append((item_id, f"Item {item_id}", score))
        
        return recommendations

class BPR:
    def __init__(self, nusers, nitems, factors=50, lr=0.01, regu=0.01, regi=0.01):
        self.nusers = nusers
        self.nitems = nitems
        self.factors = factors
        self.lr = lr
        self.regu = regu
        self.regi = regi
        
        np.random.seed(42)
        random.seed(42)
        
        initstd = 0.1
        self.U = np.random.normal(0, initstd, (nusers, factors))
        self.V = np.random.normal(0, initstd, (nitems, factors))
        
        self.losses = []
        self.aucs = []
        
    def sigmoid(self, x):
        x = np.clip(x, -500, 500)
        return 1.0 / (1.0 + np.exp(-x))
    
    def predict(self, user, item):
        return np.dot(self.U[user], self.V[item])
    
    def sampleneg(self, user, positems, maxattempts=50):
        for attempt in range(maxattempts):
            neg = random.randint(0, self.nitems - 1)
            if neg not in positems:
                return neg
        
        allitems = set(range(self.nitems))
        negcandidates = list(allitems - positems)
        if negcandidates:
            return random.choice(negcandidates)
        else:
            return random.randint(0, self.nitems - 1)
    
    def update(self, user, positem, negitem):
        pospred = self.predict(user, positem)
        negpred = self.predict(user, negitem)
        xuij = pospred - negpred
        sigmoidval = self.sigmoid(xuij)
        error = 1.0 - sigmoidval
        
        uf = self.U[user].copy()
        iF = self.V[positem].copy()
        jf = self.V[negitem].copy()
        
        self.U[user] = self.U[user] + self.lr * (error * (iF - jf) - self.regu * uf)
        self.V[positem] = self.V[positem] + self.lr * (error * uf - self.regi * iF)
        self.V[negitem] = self.V[negitem] + self.lr * (-error * uf - self.regi * jf)
        
        loss = -np.log(sigmoidval + 1e-10) + 0.5 * self.regu * np.sum(uf**2)
        loss = loss + 0.5 * self.regi * (np.sum(iF**2) + np.sum(jf**2))
        
        return loss
    
    def fit(self, traindata, testdata=None, epochs=100, verbose=True, evalevery=10):
        useritems = {}
        for user in range(len(traindata)):
            useritems[user] = set([item for item, rating in traindata[user]])
        
        activeusers = [u for u in useritems.keys() if len(useritems[u]) > 0]
        
        if verbose:
            print(f"Training BPR for {epochs} epochs on {len(activeusers)} active users")
        
        initiallr = self.lr
        
        for epoch in range(epochs):
            epochstart = time.time()
            epochloss = 0.0
            numupdates = 0
            
            if epoch > 0:
                self.lr = initiallr * (0.98 ** epoch)
            
            random.shuffle(activeusers)
            
            for user in activeusers:
                positems = useritems[user]
                if len(positems) == 0:
                    continue
                
                numsamples = min(len(positems) * 5, 50)
                
                for sample in range(numsamples):
                    positem = random.choice(list(positems))
                    negitem = self.sampleneg(user, positems)
                    
                    loss = self.update(user, positem, negitem)
                    epochloss = epochloss + loss
                    numupdates = numupdates + 1
            
            avgloss = epochloss / max(numupdates, 1)
            self.losses.append(avgloss)
            
            if testdata is not None and (epoch + 1) % evalevery == 0:
                auc = self.evalauc(testdata, useritems)
                self.aucs.append(auc)
                
                if verbose:
                    epochtime = time.time() - epochstart
                    print(f"Epoch {epoch+1:3d}/{epochs} | Time: {epochtime:.1f}s | "
                          f"Loss: {avgloss:.4f} | AUC: {auc:.4f}")
            elif verbose and (epoch + 1) % 10 == 0:
                epochtime = time.time() - epochstart
                print(f"Epoch {epoch+1:3d}/{epochs} | Time: {epochtime:.1f}s | "
                      f"Loss: {avgloss:.4f}")
    
    def evalauc(self, testdata, traindata, numsamples=1000):
        testuseritems = {}
        for user in range(len(testdata)):
            testuseritems[user] = set([item for item, rating in testdata[user]])
        
        ytrue = []
        yscores = []
        
        userswithtest = [u for u in testuseritems.keys() if len(testuseritems[u]) > 0]
        
        for sample in range(numsamples):
            if not userswithtest:
                break
            
            user = random.choice(userswithtest)
            
            if len(testuseritems[user]) > 0:
                positem = random.choice(list(testuseritems[user]))
                
                alluseritems = traindata.get(user, set()) | testuseritems.get(user, set())
                negitem = self.sampleneg(user, alluseritems)
                
                posscore = self.predict(user, positem)
                negscore = self.predict(user, negitem)
                
                ytrue.extend([1, 0])
                yscores.extend([posscore, negscore])
        
        if len(ytrue) > 0:
            return roc_auc_score(ytrue, yscores)
        else:
            return 0.5

def evalpr(model, testdata, traindata, kvalues=[5, 10, 20]):
    results = {}
    
    for k in kvalues:
        precisions = []
        recalls = []
        
        for user in range(len(testdata)):
            testitems = set([item for item, rating in testdata[user]])
            if len(testitems) == 0:
                continue
            
            trainitems = set([item for item, rating in traindata[user]])
            candidateitems = [i for i in range(model.nitems) if i not in trainitems]
            
            scores = [(item, model.predict(user, item)) for item in candidateitems]
            scores.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
            recommendations = set([item for item, score in scores[:k]])
            
            if len(recommendations) > 0:
                precision = len(recommendations & testitems) / len(recommendations)
                precisions.append(precision)
            
            if len(testitems) > 0:
                recall = len(recommendations & testitems) / len(testitems)
                recalls.append(recall)
        
        results[f'precision@{k}'] = np.mean(precisions) if precisions else 0.0
        results[f'recall@{k}'] = np.mean(recalls) if recalls else 0.0
    
    return results

Our ABTesting to do Controlled Experiments , Here we use We use deterministic hashing for consistent user assignment.¶

class ABTest:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.resultsA = []
        self.resultsB = []
        
    def hashuser(self, userid):
        hashobj = hashlib.sha256(str(userid).encode())
        hashdigest = hashobj.hexdigest()
        return 'A' if int(hashdigest[:2], 16) < 128 else 'B'
    
    def getrecommendations(self, model, useridx, topk=10, variant='control'):
        scores = []
        
        for i in range(self.data.N):
            pred = self.data.mu + model.bu[useridx] + model.bi[i]
            
            if hasattr(model, 'U') and hasattr(model, 'V'):
                pred = pred + np.dot(model.U[useridx], model.V[i])
            
            if variant == 'test':
                if hasattr(model, 'F') and self.data.features[i]:
                    genreboost = 1.0 + 0.1 * len(self.data.features[i])
                    pred = pred * genreboost
            
            scores.append((i, pred))
        
        scores.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        return [i for i, score in scores[:topk]]
    
    def simulateinteraction(self, useridx, model, variant='control'):
        recommendations = self.getrecommendations(model, useridx, topk=10, variant=variant)
        
        simulatedratings = []
        for itemidx in recommendations:
            pred = self.data.mu + model.bu[useridx] + model.bi[itemidx]
            if hasattr(model, 'U') and hasattr(model, 'V'):
                pred = pred + np.dot(model.U[useridx], model.V[itemidx])
            
            rating = np.clip(pred + np.random.normal(0, 0.5), 1, 5)
            simulatedratings.append(rating)
        
        return np.mean(simulatedratings)
    
    def runtest(self, model, nusers=100, verbose=True):
        if verbose:
            print("\n" + "="*60)
            print("A/B TEST SIMULATION")
            print("="*60)
        
        self.resultsA = []
        self.resultsB = []
        
        testusers = np.random.choice(self.data.M, min(nusers, self.data.M), replace=False)
        
        for useridx in testusers:
            userid = self.data.userlist[useridx]
            group = self.hashuser(userid)
            
            if group == 'A':
                metric = self.simulateinteraction(useridx, model, variant='control')
                self.resultsA.append(metric)
            else:
                metric = self.simulateinteraction(useridx, model, variant='test')
                self.resultsB.append(metric)
        
        tstat, pvalue = stats.ttest_ind(self.resultsA, self.resultsB)
        
        if verbose:
            print(f"Group A (Control, n={len(self.resultsA)}): Mean={np.mean(self.resultsA):.4f}")
            print(f"Group B (Test, n={len(self.resultsB)}): Mean={np.mean(self.resultsB):.4f}")
            print(f"T-statistic: {tstat:.4f}")
            print(f"P-value: {pvalue:.4f}")
            
            if pvalue < 0.05:
                winner = 'A' if np.mean(self.resultsA) > np.mean(self.resultsB) else 'B'
                print(f" Model {winner} is significantly better (p < 0.05)")
            else:
                print(" No significant difference")
        
        return {'tstat': tstat, 'pvalue': pvalue}

class Recommender:
    def __init__(self, model, data):
        self.model = model
        self.data = data
        
    def recommendformovie(self, movieid, topk=10):
        if movieid not in self.data.itemmap:
            print(f"Movie {movieid} not found")
            return []
            
        idx = self.data.itemmap[movieid]
        title = self.data.titles.get(movieid, "Unknown")
        print(f"\nRecommendations for users who liked: {title}")
        print("-" * 60)
        
        if hasattr(self.model, 'V'):
            dummyu = self.model.V[idx].copy()
        else:
            print("Model doesn't have item vectors")
            return []
        
        scores = []
        for i in range(self.data.N):
            if self.data.counts[i] >= 50:
                score = np.dot(dummyu, self.model.V[i])
                if hasattr(self.model, 'bi'):
                    score = score + 0.1 * self.model.bi[i]
                scores.append((i, score))
        
        scores.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        
        recommendations = []
        for rank, (i, score) in enumerate(scores[:topk], 1):
            mid = self.data.itemlist[i]
            title = self.data.titles.get(mid, "Unknown")[:60]
            print(f"{rank:2}. {title:<60} | Score: {score:.3f}")
            recommendations.append((mid, title, score))
            
        return recommendations

def plotcurves(model, title):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))
    
    epochs = range(len(model.rmsetrain))
    axes[0].plot(epochs, model.rmsetrain, 'b-o', label='Train', markersize=4)
    axes[0].plot(epochs, model.rmsetest, 'r-o', label='Test', markersize=4)

    axes[0].set_ylabel('RMSE')
    axes[0].set_title(f'{title} - RMSE')
    axes[0].legend()

    axes[1].set_title(f'{title} - Loss (Should Increase)')
    axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

def plotembeddings2d(model, data):
    if not hasattr(model, "V"):
        print("Model has no V")
        return
    
    V = model.V
    if V.shape[1] >= 2:
        V2d = V[:, :2]
    else:
        return 0
    uniquegenres = set()
    for i in range(data.N):
        if data.features[i]:
            primarygenreidx = data.features[i][0]
            uniquegenres.add(primarygenreidx)

    genrelist = sorted(list(uniquegenres))
    colors = plt.cm.tab20(np.linspace(0, 1, max(1, min(20, len(genrelist)))))
    genrecolors = {g: colors[i % 20] for i, g in enumerate(genrelist)}
    if hasattr(data, "counts") and data.counts is not None:
        popular = [i for i in range(data.N) if data.counts[i] >= 100]
    else:
        popular = list(range(data.N))

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    plottedgenres = set()
   
    horrorexample = None
    childrenexample = None
    
    for i in popular[:1000]:
        if not data.features[i]:
            continue

        primarygenreidx = data.features[i][0]
        genrename = data.genres[primarygenreidx]
        color = genrecolors.get(primarygenreidx, 'gray')
        x = V2d[i, 0] + (0.1 * model.bi[i] if hasattr(model, "bi") else 0.0)
        y = V2d[i, 1]
        
        if genrename == 'Horror' and horrorexample is None:
            horrorexample = (x, y, data.titles.get(data.itemlist[i], "Unknown")[:30])
        if genrename == 'Children' and childrenexample is None:
            childrenexample = (x, y, data.titles.get(data.itemlist[i], "Unknown")[:30])

        if primarygenreidx not in plottedgenres and len(plottedgenres) < 15:
            plt.scatter(x, y, c=[color], alpha=0.6, s=30, label=genrename)
            plottedgenres.add(primarygenreidx)
        else:
            plt.scatter(x, y, c=[color], alpha=0.6, s=30)
    if horrorexample:
        plt.annotate(f"Horror: {horrorexample[2]}", 
                    (horrorexample[0], horrorexample[1]),
                    xytext=(10, 10), textcoords='offset points',
                    bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.5', fc='yellow', alpha=0.5),
                    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', connectionstyle='arc3,rad=0'),
                    fontsize=8)
    
    if childrenexample:
        plt.annotate(f"Children: {childrenexample[2]}", 
                    (childrenexample[0], childrenexample[1]),
                    xytext=(-10, -10), textcoords='offset points',
                    bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.5', fc='lightblue', alpha=0.5),
                    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', connectionstyle='arc3,rad=0'),
                    fontsize=8)

    plt.title('2D Movie Embeddings - Similar Movies Cluster Together', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    plt.xlabel('Latent Dimension 1 (with bias adjustment)')
    plt.ylabel('Latent Dimension 2')
    if plottedgenres:
        plt.legend(fontsize=8, loc='best', ncol=2)
    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def plotbpr(bprmodel, prresults):

def plotdimensions(results):
    Dvalues = sorted(results.keys())
    trainrmse = [results[d]['train'] for d in Dvalues]
    testrmse = [results[d]['test'] for d in Dvalues]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(Dvalues, trainrmse, 'b-o', label='Train', linewidth=2, markersize=8)

    plt.xlabel('Number of Latent Dimensions (D)')
    plt.ylabel('RMSE')
    plt.title('Choosing Optimal Latent Dimensions - Diminishing Returns Analysis')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    
    bestd = min(results.keys(), key=lambda d: results[d]['test'])
    plt.axvline(x=bestd, color='green', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)
    plt.text(bestd, min(testrmse), f' Best: D={bestd}', fontsize=10)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def plotvi(vimodel):
    """Here We plot VI-specific metrics showing RMSE and ELBO evolution"""
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))
    
    epochs = range(len(vimodel.rmsetrain))
    axes[0].plot(epochs, vimodel.rmsetrain, 'b-o', label='Train', markersize=4)
    axes[0].plot(epochs, vimodel.rmsetest, 'r-o', label='Test', markersize=4)
    axes[0].set_xlabel('Epoch')
    axes[0].set_ylabel('RMSE')
    axes[0].set_title('Variational Inference - RMSE')
    axes[0].legend()
    axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    
    axes[1].plot(vimodel.elbohistory, 'g-', linewidth=2)
    axes[1].set_xlabel('Epoch')
    axes[1].set_ylabel('ELBO')
    axes[1].set_title('VI Evidence Lower Bound (Should Increase)')
    axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
    
    isincreasing = all(vimodel.elbohistory[i] <= vimodel.elbohistory[i+1] 
                       for i in range(len(vimodel.elbohistory)-1))
    status = " Monotonically increasing" if isincreasing else " Not monotonic"
    axes[1].text(0.02, 0.98, status, transform=axes[1].transAxes,
                fontsize=10, verticalalignment='top',
                color='green' if isincreasing else 'red')
    
    plt.suptitle('Variational Inference Performance', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def analyzeuncertainty(vimodel, data):
    itemvar = np.mean(vimodel.sigma_V, axis=1)
    
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("UNCERTAINTY ANALYSIS")
    print("="*60)
    
    sorted_indices = np.argsort(itemvar)
    
    print("\nMost Certain Items (Low Variance):")
    for rank, idx in enumerate(sorted_indices[:10], 1):
        movieid = data.itemlist[idx]
        title = data.titles.get(movieid, "Unknown")[:50]
        ratings = data.counts[idx]
        print(f"{rank:2}. {title:<50} | σ²={itemvar[idx]:.6f} | Ratings={ratings}")
    
    print("\nMost Uncertain Items (High Variance):")
    for rank, idx in enumerate(sorted_indices[-10:][::-1], 1):
        movieid = data.itemlist[idx]
        title = data.titles.get(movieid, "Unknown")[:50]
        ratings = data.counts[idx]
        print(f"{rank:2}. {title:<50} | σ²={itemvar[idx]:.6f} | Ratings={ratings}")
    
    coldstart = [idx for idx in range(data.N) if data.counts[idx] <= 5]
    popular = [idx for idx in range(data.N) if data.counts[idx] >= 1000]
    
    if coldstart:
        print(f"\nCold Start Items (≤5 ratings): Mean σ² = {np.mean(itemvar[coldstart]):.6f}")
    if popular:
        print(f"Popular Items (≥1000 ratings): Mean σ² = {np.mean(itemvar[popular]):.6f}")

coldstartdemo(): Here we demonstrate how our genre embeddings enable recommendations for new items with minimal ratings in our system.¶

def coldstartdemo(model, data):
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("COLD START DEMONSTRATION")
    print("="*60)
    
    coldstartcandidates = []
    for i in range(data.N):
        if data.counts[i] <= 3 and len(data.features[i]) > 0:
            coldstartcandidates.append(i)
    
    print(f"Found {len(coldstartcandidates)} movies with ≤3 ratings but with genres")
    
    adventureidx = data.genremap.get('Adventure', -1)
    animationidx = data.genremap.get('Animation', -1)
    
    if adventureidx >= 0 and animationidx >= 0:
        print("\nSimulating new 'Adventure + Animation' movie...")
        
        dummyfeatures = [adventureidx, animationidx]
        dummyembedding = np.sum(model.F[dummyfeatures], axis=0) / np.sqrt(len(dummyfeatures))
        
        print(f"Predicted embedding norm: {np.linalg.norm(dummyembedding):.3f}")
        
        similarities = []
        for i in range(data.N):
            if data.counts[i] >= 50:
                sim = np.dot(dummyembedding, model.V[i]) / (
                    np.linalg.norm(dummyembedding) * np.linalg.norm(model.V[i]) + 1e-10)
                similarities.append((i, sim))
        
        similarities.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        
        print("\nMost similar existing movies:")
        for rank, (i, sim) in enumerate(similarities[:5], 1):
            movieid = data.itemlist[i]
            title = data.titles.get(movieid, "Unknown")[:50]
            print(f"{rank}. {title} (similarity: {sim:.3f})")

def findpolarizing(model, data, topk=10):
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("POLARIZING MOVIES")
    print("="*60)
    
    norms = []
    for i in range(data.N):
        if data.counts[i] >= 100:
            norm = np.linalg.norm(model.V[i])
            norms.append((i, norm))
    
    norms.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    
    print("\nMost Polarizing (large ||v||):")
    for rank, (i, norm) in enumerate(norms[:topk], 1):
        title = data.titles.get(data.itemlist[i], "Unknown")[:50]
        print(f"{rank:2}. {title:<50} | ||v||={norm:.3f}")
    
    print("\nLeast Polarizing (small ||v||):")
    for rank, (i, norm) in enumerate(norms[-topk:], 1):
        title = data.titles.get(data.itemlist[i], "Unknown")[:50]
        print(f"{rank:2}. {title:<50} | ||v||={norm:.3f}")

tune(): Here we do our hyperparameter optimization where we conduct grid search over $\lambda$, $\gamma$, and $\tau$ in our model.¶

In [51]:
def tune(data):
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("HYPERPARAMETER TUNING")
    print("="*60)
    
    params = [
        {'lam': 0.1, 'gam': 2.5, 'tau': 1.0},
        {'lam': 0.2, 'gam': 2.5, 'tau': 1.0},
        {'lam': 0.1, 'gam': 5.0, 'tau': 2.0}
    ]
    
    bestparams = None
    bestrmse = float('inf')
    
    for p in params:
        model = Latent(data)
        model.train(D=10, epochs=5, verbose=False, **p)
        testrmse = model.rmsetest[-1]
        print(f"λ={p['lam']}, γ={p['gam']}, τ={p['tau']} -> Test RMSE: {testrmse:.4f}")
        
        if testrmse < bestrmse:
            bestrmse = testrmse
            bestparams = p
    
    print(f"\nBest params: λ={bestparams['lam']}, γ={bestparams['gam']}, τ={bestparams['tau']}")
    print(f"Best RMSE: {bestrmse:.4f}")
    return bestparams

dimensionanalysis(): Here we have our analysis where we determine optimal latent dimensions by examining our performance-complexity trade-off by testing different dimenstions.¶

def dimensionanalysis(data, bestparams):
    print("\n" + "="*60)
    print("DIMENSION ANALYSIS")
    print("="*60)
    
    Dvalues = [2, 5, 10, 20, 50]
    dimensionresults = {}
    
    for D in Dvalues:
        model = Latent(data)
        model.train(D=D, epochs=10, verbose=False, **bestparams)
        dimensionresults[D] = {
            'train': model.rmsetrain[-1],
            'test': model.rmsetest[-1]
        }
        print(f"D={D:2} -> Train: {model.rmsetrain[-1]:.4f}, Test: {model.rmsetest[-1]:.4f}")
    
    plotdimensions(dimensionresults)
    
    optimald = min(dimensionresults.keys(), key=lambda d: dimensionresults[d]['test'])
    return optimald
